1)pipes -
Pipes are simple functions used in templates to transform data for display. They don't change the data itself, just how it looks to the user.
{{ birthday | date:'shortDate' }}

2) Services
Services are classes that encapsulate reusable logic or data fetching. They are typically injected into components using Dependency Injection (DI).
@Injectable()

3)interceptor
Interceptors act as a "middleman" for your HTTP requests and responses
between your code and the outside world
4) guards
used to protect routes.
It sits between the user's click and the component they want to see.
They determine if a user has permission to navigate to (or away from) a specific part of the app.

CanActivate: Can the user enter this route? (e.g., Are they logged in?)

CanDeactivate: Can the user leave? (e.g., "You have unsaved changes.")

CanMatch: Should this route even be considered?


