directives--
instructions that tell Angular how to change the appearance or behavior of elements in the DOM (Document Object Model)
- Structural Directives --- These change the structure of the DOM by adding, removing, or manipulating elements. They are easily identified by an asterisk (*) before the directive name.
*ngIf: Conditionally adds or removes an element based on a true/false value.

*ngFor: Loops through a list (array) and creates an element for each item.

*ngSwitch: Functions like a switch statement in programming to show one element among many options.

- Attribute Directives

These change the appearance or behavior of an existing element, component, or another directive. Unlike structural directives, they do not add or remove elements from the DOM.

ngModel: Used for two-way data binding (as we discussed).

ngClass: Dynamically adds or removes multiple CSS classes.

ngStyle: Dynamically sets multiple inline CSS styles.


